<br>
Hey, I feel bad for the guy's mother, but what exactly is she trying to prove? Please keep your uninformed, ignorant ass away from my hobby. The majority of that article was laughable.  Some of my favorite lines whould include these classics:<br>
<br>
&quot;The manufacturer of EverQuest purposely made it in such a way that it is more intriguing to the addict,&quot; Parker said. &quot;It could be created in a less addictive way, but (that) would be the difference between powdered cocaine and crack cocaine.&quot;<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
&quot;After playing the game for 36 hours straight, he had a psychotic break because of sleep deprivation, Parker said.<br>
&quot;He thought the characters had come out of the game and were chasing him,&quot; Parker said. &quot;He was running through his neighborhood having hallucinations. I can't think of a drug he could have taken where he would have disintegrated in 15 weeks.&quot;<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
&quot;The other piece is that it takes time to leave the game. You have to find a place to hide to get out, and that makes people want to play longer.&quot;<br>
<br>
I read these and LAUGHED.  I'm sorry if that's insensitive, but OMG that's insanely hilarious stuff right there!  <br>
<br>
<br>
Warning labels are just about the most useless waste of space on the entire planet. Hey, maybe if we put &quot;please don't shoot people&quot; labels on every gun, no one would get shot anymore! WTF are they thinking? *boggle* <br>
<br>
Thanks for saving the world from itself lady. If Sony is forced to put your label on EQ, the world can thank you for kickstarting the perfect Utopia we have never been able to achieve until your personal crusade. <br>
<br>
Whatever happened to people being responsible for thier own actions?  If EQ hadn't caused his suicide, I'm certian Marylin Manson or Blade II would've been the final straw.  The only thing for certian is that SOMETHING would've casued him to pull that trigger...certianly not his own, personal problems.  Choose one, he had many.<br>
<br>
